ub Am\u00e9rica\n* [[Mexican Primera Divisi\u00f3n]] (1): [[Primera Divisi\u00f3n de M\u00e9xico Verano 2002|Verano 2002]]\n\n===International===\n; Chile\n* [[Summer Olympic|Olympic Bronze Medal]] (1): [[Football at the 2000 Summer Olympics|2000]]\n\n===Individual===\n* [[Swiss Footballer of the Year#Foreigner of the Year|Swiss Super League Best Foreign Player]] (1): 1989\u201390\n* [[Trofeo EFE|EFE Trophy]] (2): 1992\u201393, 1994\u201395\n* [[Pichichi Trophy]] (1): 1994\u201395\n* [[Don Bal\u00f3n Award|La Liga Best Foreign Player]] (1): 1994-95\n* [[European Sports Media#1994\u201395|European Sports Media Team of the Year]] (1): 1994-95\n* [[Olympic Games]] top scorer (1): [[Football at the 2000 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's tournament|2000]]\n* [[FIFA 100]]\n* The Football History Boys Top 250 Players of All-Time #249 <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thefootballhistoryboys.com/2014/01/the-top-250-250-241.html|title=The Top 250 Players of All-Time: 250-241}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Iv\u00e1n Zamorano}}\n* [http://www.inter.it/es/archivio_giocatore/G0680# Inter profile] {{in lang|it}}\n* [http://www.rsssf.com/miscellaneous/zamorano-intlg.html Iv\u00e1n Luis Zamorano - Detail of international matches and goals] - rsssf.com ([[RSSSF]]).\n* {{BDFutbol|1158}}\n* {{NFT player|pid=13677}}\n\n{{Navboxes colour\n|bg=gold\n|fg=navy\n|title= Awards\n|list1=\n{{Swiss Footballer of the Year}}\n{{FIFA 100}}\n{{Copa Chile topscorers}}\n{{Olympic top scorers}}\n{{La Liga top scorers}}\n{{La Liga Foreign Player of the Year}}\n{{Swiss Super League top scorers}}\n{{Chilean Footballer of the Year}}\n{{Trofeo EFE}}\n}}\n{{Navboxes colour\n|title=Chile squads\n|bg= red\n|fg= white\n|bordercolor= gray\n|list1=\n{{Chile Squad 1987 Copa Am\u00e9rica}}\n{{Chile Squad 1991 Copa Am\u00e9rica}}\n{{Chile Squad 1993 Copa Am\u00e9rica }}\n{{Chile Squad 1998 World Cup}}\n{{Chile Squad 1999 Copa Am\u00e9rica}}\n{{Chile Squad 2000 Summer Olympi